(88, 'Battery Tester Price in BD', 600, 100, 700, 'battery-tester_01.png', 'Battery Tester, Household Digital Battery Checker for Pencil AA, Pencil AAA Batteries & Button Cells etc. Test multiple sizes of batteries in one unit.\r\nTests: AA (pencil cells), AAA, 9 V batteries all kinds of button cells.\r\nEasy one push test  Just fit the battery in the sliding arm, and the scale will move to show the power level. For 9 V batteries use side panel contacts.', 4.40, 'Black', 10, 7, 1, 500, '<p id=\"isPasted\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Product features:</span></strong></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 40px;\">Easy to read. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 40px;\">Quickly test the battery level.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 40px;\">Compact size and lightweight design.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 40px;\">Self-powered, no need for internal battery.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 40px;\">Test multiple battery sizes in one unit.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 40px;\">Checks the power level of 9V and 1.5V batteries.</p><p><br></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Specification:</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">1.5 V: AAA, HP6, MN2400, RO3, AA, HP7, MN1500, HP11, MN1400, UM2, D, HP2, MN1300, UM1 and button cell.</p><p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">9V - PP3, MN1604, 6F22, 006P.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 40px;\">Red = Replace</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 40px;\">Yellow = Low Power</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 40px;\">Green = Good</p><p><img src=\"https://robomartbd.com/uploads/uploads/froala_editor/images/battery-tester_03.png\" style=\"width: 300px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\"></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Description:</span></strong></p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 14px;\">Two buttons on the side for testing 9 volt batteries</li><li style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 14px;\">Test multiple sizes of batteries in one unit</li><li style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 14px;\">Tests: AA (pencil cells), AAA, 9 V batteries all kinds of button cells.</li><li style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 14px;\">Easy one push test &ndash; Just fit the battery in the sliding arm, and the scale will move to show the power level. For 9 V batteries use side panel contacts. A very compact, portable and useful gadget, must have for every home and office. Small and convenient: Simple but efficient small AA, AAA battery tester verifier (BT-168D) compact size and lightweight, easy to carry.</li><li style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 14px;\">Versatile use: can test different types of household batteries such as AA, AAA, C, D, 1.5V, 9V and 1.5V button types.</li><li style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 14px;\">No power required: This battery monitor does it all. Easy-to-read analog display hand moves to quickly identify battery status &quot;good&quot; (green), &quot;low&quot; (yellow) and &quot;replace/recharge&quot; (red). Great for emergencies, this universal battery tester is powered by the batteries it tests.</li><li style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 14px;\">Easy to read: the number indicates the power level. No battery required. It is activated by the battery being checked.</li><li style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 14px;\">The battery charge tester comes with guaranteed quality: we want you to enjoy your battery testers to the fullest! We will provide a full refund or exchange if you are not excited about your simple and portable battery charge indicator.</li></ul><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Package contains:</span></strong></p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1 x Battery Tester (Battery not included)</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>', '<p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>', 'BT-0008'),
(89, 'DC Power Supply - Vantek DPS3305P Price in BD', 10550, 450, 11000, 'Power-supply_01.png', 'power supply High efficiency, low power consumption and long service life. This power supply adopts high quality aluminum material, strong heat dissipation performance.', 4.90, 'Black & White', 10, 8, 1, 9500, '<p id=\"isPasted\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">SPECIFICATION:</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Name: Program DC power supply</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Brand: Vantek</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Model: DPS3305P</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Voltage output: 0-32.00V</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Current output: 0-5.000A</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Source effect: CV&le; 0.01% + 3mV (mA)</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Load effect: CV&le; 0.01% + 3mV (I&le; 3A); CC&le; 0.2% + 3mA (I&le; 3A)</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">CV&le; 0.02% + 5mV (I&gt; 3A); CC&le; 0.2% + 5mA (I&gt; 3A)</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Ripple and noise: CV&le; l.0mVrms (I&le; 3A); CC&le; 3marms (I&le; 3A);</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">CV&le; 2.0mVrms (I&gt; 3A); CC&le; 6mArms (I&gt; 3A)</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Protection Type: Over Current Protection (OCP) Over Voltage Protection (OVP)</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Voltage accuracy: &plusmn; (Values read 0.5% + 2 bits)</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Current accuracy: &plusmn; (Values read 1% + 2 bits)</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Environmental humidity: &le; 80%</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Voltage: 110-220V ac 50Hz / 60Hz</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Wattage: 160W</p><p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">Weight: 4kg</p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://robomartbd.com/uploads/uploads/froala_editor/images/Power-supply_02.png\" style=\"width: 300px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\"></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">DESCRIPTION:</span></strong></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 20px;\">This power supply is analog and digital control technology integrated into a new general purpose power supply.It has high stability analog power, low noise ripple characteristics of digital circuits and easy to operate, and also has various control functions. Selected output power can be monitored using a 4-digit seven segment display unit, for voltage as well as current. &nbsp;Such types of display are used to ensure no lagging and clear visualization on indoor and outdoor surfaces. High efficiency, low power consumption and long service life. This power supply adopts high quality aluminum material, strong heat dissipation performance.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 20px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Package contains:</span></strong></p><p>1x &nbsp;DC Power Supply - Vantek DPS3305P</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>', '<p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>', 'BT-0009'),
(90, 'Arduino Uno R3 SMD Price in BD', 2690, 310, 3000, 'uno_01.png', 'The Arduino UNO is the best board to get started with electronics and coding. If this is your first experience tinkering with the platform, the UNO is the most robust board you can start playing with. The UNO is the most used and documented board of the whole Arduino family.', 4.90, 'Blue', 50, 9, 1, 2000, '<p id=\"isPasted\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Features:</span></strong></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Arduino UNO R3 - DIP development board &amp; USB cable&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Microcontroller: ATmega328 SMD</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">1.0 pinout: added SDA and SCL pins that are near to the AREF pin and two other new pins placed near to the RESET pin, the IOREF that allow the shields to adapt to the voltage provided from the board</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Stronger RESET circuit</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Atmega 16U2 replaces the 8U2</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Comes with USB cable&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><img src=\"https://robomartbd.com/uploads/uploads/froala_editor/images/uno_02.png\" style=\"width: 300px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\"></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Specification:</span></strong></p><p>Microcontroller: ATmega328</p><p>Operating Voltage: 5V</p><p>Input Voltage (recommended): 7-12V</p><p>Input Voltage (limits): 6-20V</p><p>Digital I/O Pins: 14 (of which 6 provide PWM output)</p><p>Analog Input Pins: 6</p><p>DC Current per I/O Pin: 40 mA</p><p>DC Current for 3.3V Pin: 50 mA</p><p>Flash Memory: 32 KB (ATmega328) of which 0.5 KB used by bootloader</p><p>SRAM: 2 KB (ATmega328)</p><p>EEPROM: 1 KB (ATmega328)</p><p>Clock Speed: 16 MHz</p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><img src=\"https://robomartbd.com/uploads/uploads/froala_editor/images/uno_01.png\" style=\"width: 300px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\"></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Description:</span></strong></p><p>The Arduino Uno Rev3 SMD is a microcontroller board based on the ATmega328. It has 14 digital input/output pins (of which 6 can be used as PWM outputs), 6 analog inputs, a 16 MHz ceramic resonator (CSTCE16M0V53-R0), a USB connection, a power jack, an ICSP header, and a reset button. Arduino UNO SMD is a microcontroller board based on the ATmega328P. It has 14 digital input/output pins (of which 6 can be used as PWM outputs), 6 analog inputs, a 16 MHz ceramic resonator, a USB connection, a power jack, an ICSP header and a reset button. It contains everything needed to support the microcontroller; simply connect it to a computer with a USB cable or power it with a AC-to-DC adapter or battery to get started.</p><p><br></p><p id=\"isPasted\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Package Includes:</span></strong></p><p>1 x Arduino UNO SMD</p><p>1 x USB Cable</p><p>1 x Male header connector single row</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>', '<p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>', 'ARD-0007'),
