(94, 'Arduino Micro R3 Price in BD', 1380, 120, 1500, 'ARD_01_VDTXf0v.png', 'Microcontroller: The Arduino Micro R3 is based on the ATmega32U4 microcontroller, which provides a 32-bit processing power and a wide range of features. USB Interface: The board features a Micro-USB interface, which allows it to be easily connected to a computer or other USB devices.', 4.50, 'Blue', 30, 7, 1, 1000, '<p style=\'margin-right:0in;margin-left:0in;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:7.5pt;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:justify;background:white;\' id=\"isPasted\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><strong>Features:</strong></span></p><ol style=\"list-style-type: decimal;margin-left:0in;\"><li><span style=\'font-family:\"Helvetica\",sans-serif;font-size:11.5pt;color:#333333;\'>Microcontroller: The Arduino Micro R3 is based on the ATmega32U4 microcontroller, which provides a 32-bit processing power and a wide range of features.</span></li><li><span style=\'font-family:\"Helvetica\",sans-serif;font-size:11.5pt;color:#333333;\'>USB Interface: The board features a Micro-USB interface, which allows it to be easily connected to a computer or other USB devices.</span></li><li><span style=\'font-family:\"Helvetica\",sans-serif;font-size:11.5pt;color:#333333;\'>Digital I/O Pins: The Arduino Micro R3 has 20 digital input/output pins, including 7 pins that can be used as PWM outputs, providing a wide range of connectivity options.</span></li><li><span style=\'font-family:\"Helvetica\",sans-serif;font-size:11.5pt;color:#333333;\'>Analog Inputs: The board also has 12 analog inputs, which provide a high resolution of conversion for analog signals.</span></li><li><span style=\'font-family:\"Helvetica\",sans-serif;font-size:11.5pt;color:#333333;\'>Compatible with Arduino IDE: The Arduino Micro R3 is fully compatible with the popular Arduino Integrated Development Environment (IDE), making it easy for users to write and upload code to the board.</span></li></ol><p style=\'margin-right:0in;margin-left:0in;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:justify;\'><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p style=\'margin-right:0in;margin-left:0in;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:7.5pt;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:justify;background:white;\'><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><strong>Applications:</strong></span></p><ol style=\"list-style-type: decimal;margin-left:0in;\"><li><span style=\'font-family:\"Helvetica\",sans-serif;font-size:11.5pt;color:#333333;\'>Robotics: The small size and powerful features of the Arduino Micro R3 make it a popular choice for building small robots and controlling various actuators and sensors.</span></li><li><span style=\'font-family:\"Helvetica\",sans-serif;font-size:11.5pt;color:#333333;\'>Home Automation: The board can be used to build home automation systems, such as controlling lights, fans, and other household appliances.</span></li><li><span style=\'font-family:\"Helvetica\",sans-serif;font-size:11.5pt;color:#333333;\'>Musical Instruments: The PWM outputs and analog inputs on the Arduino Micro R3 make it ideal for building custom electronic musical instruments and sound effects generators.</span></li><li><span style=\'font-family:\"Helvetica\",sans-serif;font-size:11.5pt;color:#333333;\'>Wearable Devices: Due to its compact size and low power consumption, the Arduino Micro R3 is commonly used in the development of wearable devices and e-textiles.</span></li><li><span style=\'font-family:\"Helvetica\",sans-serif;font-size:11.5pt;color:#333333;\'>Internet of Things (IoT): The board can be used as a building block for IoT projects, such as connecting sensors and actuators to the Internet for remote monitoring and control.</span></li></ol><p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0i